<paragraph blockId="19.[178,1086,589,699]" pageId="19" pageNumber="948">
R e m a r k s: A very rare species with until now a very scattered distribution pattern. Female and hostplant are still unknown. Additional research is necessary. The taxonomic position suggested in the original description (GORBUNOV &amp; ŠPATENKA 2001) should be redefined. The species is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="LE CERF 1938" authorityName="LE CERF" authorityYear="1938" box="[591,951,677,699]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Chamaesphecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="948" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mirza">
<emphasis box="[591,808,677,699]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="948">Chamaesphecia mirza</emphasis>
LE CERF 1938
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1010,1052,678,699]" name="Iran" pageId="19" pageNumber="948">Iran</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
